reviews.review_text:
Boston Garden My first show...in the rafters a mile away...fresh from Fort Dix ..NRPS opened...last Vodka trip and future sister in law paying the way.

   The MBTA was running when we left for Wheelock College the BeeGees were still decent music.

  Let it be said I might've been the first Boom Box Bopper listening to Europe 72 /8 track on a two pc Sony portable...skipping to work at the base.. And Cream Puff War was on the radio that day.
  My Army locker was a Self doodled Fillmore Poster...wish I had a picture.
  I remember WMMR in Philly advertising a show with Tennessee Jed.
Just one song It is off but it is off by one track.

my first this was may first show of so many i lost count, my pal at the time won 2 tix on wbcn fm radio out of boston, we took the T in from newton, get in ,got to our seats, last row of the last row in the back,ithink n.r.p.s ,was the opening act,anyway,we had one joint for the night,but being only 15 we had a blast,i did knot see them till 76 in hartford then i slowley get on the bus,i saw about 125 to 140 shows,till 91 when the sudo ones get ther ohwell,but all and all i would do it all over one more time.
